EDISON MISSION OPERATION AND MAINTENANCE OPERATES THE PIPELINE UNDER CONTRACT WITH SUNRISE POWER COMPANY, LLC.  THE PIPELINE RECEIVES ITS GAS SUPPLY FROM A METERED CONNECTION AT THE KERN/MOJAVE NATURAL GAS PIPELINE, AND TRAVELS TWO MILES UNDERGROUND IN A GENERALLY WESTERLY DIRECTION TO THE SITE BOUNDARY CROSSING UNDER TWO ROADWAYS; ONE COUNTY ROAD (SHALE ROAD), AND THE OTHER A STATE HIGHWAY (HIGHWAY 33). THESE TWO ROAD CROSSINGS ARE LOCATED AT 1 MILE NORTH OF MIDWAY ROAD AND HWY 33 AND 1 MILE SOUTH OF THE INTERSECTION OF HIGHWAY 33 AND SHALE ROAD.    THIS PIPELINE IS DESIGNED, INSTALLED AND TESTED IN ACCORDANCE WITH ASME B31.8 - GAS TRANSMISSION AND DISTRIBUTION SYSTEMS, 1995 EDITION AND THE U.S. DEPARTMENT OF TRANSPORTATION, PIPELINE SAFETY REGULATIONS, NATURAL GAS PARTS 191-192.
